{{Infobox Bishopric | border = catholic | font_color = black | bishopric = [[Port Harcourt]] | coatofarms = | image = | incumbent = [[Camillus Archibong Etokudoh]] | province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Calabar|Calabar]] | diocese = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Port Harcourt|Port Harcourt]] | cathedral = [[Corpus Christi Cathedral (Port Harcourt)|Corpus Christi Cathedral]] | first_bishop = [[Godfrey Okoye]] | date = 1961 | website = }}
The '''Bishop of Port Harcourt''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|Ordinary]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Port Harcourt]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Calabar]], Nigeria.
The diocese covers an area of 21,850 km<sup>2</sup> (8,440 square miles). The [[Episcopal see]] is in [[Port Harcourt]] where the bishop's seat (''[[cathedra]]'') is located at the [[Corpus Christi Cathedral (Port Harcourt)|Corpus Christi Cathedral]], [[D-line, Port Harcourt|D-line]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bishop Ordains 10 Catholic Priests|url=http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/2013/07/29/bishop-ordains-10-catholic-priests/|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=[[The Tide (Nigeria)|The Tide]]|date=29 July 2013}}</ref> The current bishop is the Most Reverend [[Camillus Archibong Etokudoh]], the third Bishop of Port Harcourt.
