[[File:Deserto Viana, Boa Vista.jpg|thumb|right|''Deserto de Viana'' in northwestern Boa Vista Island]]
The '''Deserto de Viana''' is a sand desert in the northwestern part of the island of [[Boa Vista, Cape Verde|Boa Vista]], [[Cape Verde]]. It is situated east of the towns [[Rabil]] and [[Sal Rei]], and west of [[Bofarreira]]. The desert itself is not a protected area, but it is adjacent to the nature reserve ''Boa Esperança'', which includes the [[Lagoa do Rabil]] and the [[Praia de Atalanta]].<ref name=munic>[http://www.municipiodaboavista.com/boavista-capoverde/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Espa%C3%A7os-protegidos-da-Boa-Vista.pdf Protected areas in the island of Boa Vista] - Municipality of Boa Vista, March 2013 {{pt icon}}</ref>

