The following is a timeline of the [[Matanzas#History|history]] of the city of [[Matanzas]], [[Cuba]].
{{Dynamic list}}
{{TOC right}}

==Prior to 20th century==
{{History of Cuba}}

* 1694 - [[Ayuntamiento]] (town council) established.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}}
* 1813 - Francisco Camero sets up first publishing business in Matanzas.{{sfn|Bonavía|2003}}<ref>{{cite book|title=Diccionario biográfico cubano |author=Francisco Calcagno |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KpJOAQAAMAAJ|year=1878|publisher=N. Ponce de Leon |location=New York |language=es }}</ref>
* 1815 - Mantanzas becomes capital of its department.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}}
* 1818 - Custom house built.{{sfn|Santana García|2011}}
* 1835 - Public library established.<ref>{{citation |url=http://bvs.sld.cu/revistas/aci/vol14_1_06/aci10106.htm |language=es |title=Breve reseña sobre la biblioteca pública en Cuba antes de 1959 |author=Miguel Viciedo Valdés |work=[[Acimed]] |issn=1024-9435 |publisher=Centro Nacional de Informacion de Ciencias Medicas |location=Havana |year=2005 |volume=14 |number=1 }}</ref>
* 1844
** {{Interlanguage link multi|Gabriel de la Concepción Valdés|es}} executed.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}}
** Hurricane occurs.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}}
* 1846 - Hurricane occurs.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}}
* 1853 - [[William R. King]] takes the oath for [[Vice President of the United States]] in Matanzas.
* 1863 - [[Sauto Theater]] opens.{{sfn|Bonavía|2003}}
* 1870 - Hermitage of Monteserrate established on hill near city.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}}
* 1873 - Matanzas Baseball Club formed.<ref name=perez2008>{{cite book|author=Louis A. Pérez Jr.|title=On Becoming Cuban: Identity, Nationality, and Culture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u-VRqkpThREC|orig-year= 1999 |year=2008 |publisher= [[University of North Carolina Press]] |isbn=978-1-4696-0141-0}}</ref>
* 1880 - November: International exhibition held in Matanzas.{{sfn|Figarola y Caneda|1881}}
* 1884 - ''El Correo de Matanzas'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name=Ayer1902>{{citation |publisher=[[N. W. Ayer & Son]] |location=Philadelphia |year=1902 |title= American Newspaper Annual |chapter=Cuba: Matanzas |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ie1VAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA984 }}</ref>
* 1892 - Population: 27,000.<ref>{{cite book |title=[[Statesman's Year-Book]] |year=1895 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= Spain: Colonies: Cuba and Porto Rico |chapterurl= https://hdl.handle.net/2027/njp.32101072368325?urlappend=%3Bseq=1004 }}</ref>
* 1894 - El Club de Ciclistas de Matanzas active (bicycle club) (approximate date).<ref name=perez2008 />
* 1899 - Population: 36,374 city; 45,282 district; 292,444 province.<ref>{{cite book |author=[[United States Department of War|War Department]] |title=Census of Cuba, 1899 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cs0tAAAAIAAJ |year=1900 |publisher=[[United States Government Publishing Office|Government Printing Office]] |location=Washington DC }}</ref>
* 1900 - ''El Heraldo Espanol'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name=Ayer1902 />

==20th century==

* 1907 - Population: 36,009 city; 64,385 municipality; 239,812 province.<ref>{{cite book|editor1= Victor H. Olmsted |editor2= [[Henry Gannett]] |title=Cuba: Population, History and Resources 1907 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=m2czAQAAIAAJ |year=1909|publisher=[[United States Bureau of the Census]] |location=Washington DC }}</ref>
* 1912 - [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Matanzas]] established.<ref name=katolsk>{{cite web |title=Chronology of Catholic Dioceses: Cuba |url= http://www.katolsk.no/organisasjon/verden/chronology/cuba |publisher=[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Oslo]] |location=Norway |accessdate= September 25, 2016 }}</ref>
* 1916 - Teatro Velasco opens.<ref name=cinema>{{cite web |url= http://cinematreasures.org/theaters/cuba/matanzas?status=all |title=Movie Theaters in Matanzos, Cuba |work=CinemaTreasures.org |publisher= Cinema Treasures LLC |location=Los Angeles, USA |accessdate= September 25, 2016 }}</ref>
* 1919 - Population: 62,638.<ref>{{cite book |title=[[Statesman's Year-Book]] |year=1921 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= Cuba |chapterurl= http://hdl.handle.net/2027/njp.32101072368440?urlappend=%3Bseq=836 }}</ref>
* 1952 - [[Los Muñequitos de Matanzas]] [[Cuban rumba|rumba]] group formed.<ref name="Bodenheimer2015">{{cite book|author= Rebecca M. Bodenheimer |title= Geographies of Cubanidad: Place, Race, and Musical Performance in Contemporary Cuba|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lRxlCgAAQBAJ|year=2015|publisher= [[University Press of Mississippi]] |location=USA |isbn=978-1-62674-684-8}}</ref>
* 1966 - Population: 81,000.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Population of Cuba |author=Alfonso González |journal= Caribbean Studies |publisher=[[University of Puerto Rico, Río Piedras Campus]] |volume=11 |year= 1971 |jstor=25612382 }}</ref>
* 1968 - Archivo Historico Provincial de Matanzas (archives) established.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.atenas.cult.cu |language=es |title=Atenas: el Portal de la Cultura Matancera |publisher= Dirección Provincial Matanzas |accessdate=September 25, 2016 }}</ref>
* 1976 - Centro Universitario de Matanzas and Instituto Superior Pedagogico de Matanzas established.<ref name=Universities1992>{{cite book|author= [[International Association of Universities]] |title=World List of Universities |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uhmxCwAAQBAJ|year=1992 |edition=19th |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |isbn=978-1-349-12037-6 |chapter=Cuba |pages=150–152 }}</ref>
* 1978 - {{Interlanguage link multi|Jardín botánico de Matanzas|es}} (garden) established.
* 1984 - Population: 104,583 (estimate).<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1980_round.htm |title=1985 Demographic Yearbook |year=1987 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=247-289 }}</ref>
* 1999 - Population: 124,754 city;  658,100 province.<ref name=Europa2002>{{cite book|title=South America, Central America and the Caribbean 2002|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o9ODxqsr-dIC|year=2001|publisher=[[Europa Publications]]|isbn=978-1-85743-121-6 |series=Regional Surveys of the World }}</ref>

==21st century==

* 2014 - Population: 136,486.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/dyb2014.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 2014 |publisher=[[United Nations Statistics Division]] |title=Population of Capital Cities and Cities of 100,000 or More Inhabitants }}</ref>

